{
  "stem": "20142.9",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That we have to go on with life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And through hard work and through a real devotion to other people problems of participating in the daily life, we perhaps can eliminate and go to bed tired to get a full day's, full night's sleep without being affected by any unnecessary dreams.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I read quite a few books on Holocaust, and the atrocities, and the experiences of other people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was affected by it to a point that I did not understand, why didn't these people who were complaining about the nightmares and things like this, seek the professional advice to release them and provide them with a few more years of better life without suffering.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Out of the whole group that I know that we are in contact, these people are somehow living in fairly good condition, except one in Haifa that is fairly sick.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he's constantly blaming himself that he couldn't find his brother, that he claim that he's alive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was trying to help him through the-- belonging through the Holocaust Museum charter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Being a charter member, I had the possibility of seeking information of certain individuals on their original name who arrive at a certain time in United States from various places.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And unfortunately, I could not have the heart to deliver to him the news that I couldn't find it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was very, very upset about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I had to also to realize that it is better to face the truth than go on and make false promises.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "During my life, I encounter people on the basis of a straightforward approach.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was always happy when they responded in the most warmest way a individual could expect.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
